<br>
• <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Duration</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Let's face it, the current 36 second duration is almost laughable with a recast time of 72 minutes, not to mention the sheer amount of time and hitpoints it takes to down the majority of the high-end Luclin mobs. I would propose that a pet with Frenzied Burnout should act much like the Rage of Zomm pet, fixated on one target for the entire duration of the fight, ending with a kamikaze*.<br>
<br>
• <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Kamikaze*</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Get rid of this silly area effect gibberish, and turn this into unresistable direct damage, similar to a harmtouch. Spouting out numbers would make me look like a fool, so possibly start out with a base number for damage, by which the damage is lowered as the fight duration extends. The longer the fight, the less kamikaze damage. Simple as that. <br>
<br>
